      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) below 5% for hemolysis-relevant quantities of interest at the selected mesh resolution.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted using meshes of 2.1M, 5.8M, and 14.2M cells. GCI computed per Celik et al. (2008) procedure. GCI for RH index at worst-case operating point: 2.3%. GCI for peak shear stress: 3.8%. Both values satisfy the 5% threshold. The 5.8M cell mesh was selected for production runs, achieving GCI below threshold at reduced computational cost. Discretization error is well-characterised and acceptably bounded."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
