      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation (RH index, pressure head) are directly relevant to the COU decision criterion.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the relative hemolysis index (RH), which is the direct acceptance criterion for the COU (RH < 1 versus predicate device). Pressure head is a secondary QoI confirming flow-field fidelity. Both QoIs are directly mapped to the COU decision. Shear stress distributions are intermediate QoIs supporting physical plausibility. QoI relevance is high and directly traceable to the regulatory acceptance criterion."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
