      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not assessed at MRL 2; commercial solver with documented verification record is accepted.",
      "rationale": "Numerical solver error beyond discretization is not assessed at MRL 2 for a commercial solver with an established verification record. Iterative convergence was monitored via residual reduction to 1e-5 for all equations and confirmed stable mass balance closure. No anomalous solver behaviour was observed. Residual monitoring constitutes the minimum acceptable practice at this risk level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not assessed at MRL 2; simulation setup review by a second analyst is accepted as sufficient.",
      "rationale": "A peer review of simulation setup files was conducted by a second CFD analyst prior to production runs. Boundary condition assignments, material property inputs, and turbulence model settings were independently confirmed. No discrepancies were identified. Formal use error quantification is not required at MRL 2 and has not been performed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and hemolysis damage model selection justified by reference to published comparative studies for rotary blood pump flows.",
      "rationale": "The SST k-omega turbulence model was selected based on published comparative studies demonstrating superior performance in rotating machinery flows with adverse pressure gradients relative to k-epsilon variants. The power-law hemolysis damage model (Giersiepen et al.) was applied as the established standard for RH index computation in pump hemolysis assessment. Both model form choices are consistent with current best practice for this class of device and flow regime. Model form uncertainty is acknowledged as an accepted residual at MRL 2."
    },
